 To install a GitHub project locally in Python, you can follow these steps:
 1. Clone the Repository: Open a terminal or command prompt and navigate to the directory where you want to clone the project.
  example: git clone https://github.com/username/repository.git
  
2. Install Dependencies: (Check if the project has a requirements.txt file containing the required dependencies.)
pip install -r requirements.txt

3.Run the Project
python main.py

How to use the investment calculator - I attached the screenshots to prove that the computer is working.
The user has to press run and in regards to the type os the calculator will be asked more questions, as interest rates, number of months etc
